tafsir[7]{c,v,t}:
  70,12,"Or give his wife and brother in ransom."
  70,13,"Or his closest relatives who would stand with him in the face of difficulties."
  70,22,"Except for those who perform prayer; they are safe from these blameworthy traits."
  70,23,"Those who are punctual with their prayers; they are not distracted from them and they perform them at their fixed times."
  70,26,"And those who believe in the Day of Judgement: the day Allah will requite everyone with whatever they deserve."
  70,29,"And those who safeguard their private parts by concealing them and keeping them away from shameful acts."
  70,36,"O Messenger! What is it that has led these idolaters around you to reject you so quickly?"